notesStmt.note: Title from colophon (f. 178r); alternate title Śaunakasmṛti supplied by cataloger.
179 leaves foliated 1-177, [178], [i], upper left and lower right verso.
Mistakes blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; vertical margins marked with double red line.
Watermarks of the date 1838, the initials W.S., and a coat of arms of Britannia.
A single wooden board supports the manuscript.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Collection of various works on ancient Hindu laws (dharma), rites and customs, possibly attributed to the ancient sage Śaunaka (f. 178r) as well as other writers.
